    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;Approximately 212 RFCs so far, starting with RFC 269, contain the terms `foo', `bar', or `foobar' as metasyntactic variables without any proper explanation or definition.  This document rectifies that deficiency.  This memo provides information for the Internet community.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
